.SH NAME
lock_page_memcg \- lock a page and memcg binding
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct mem_cgroup *" lock_page_memcg
.BI "(struct page *page "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "page" 12
the page
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function protects unlocked LRU pages from being moved to
another cgroup.

It ensures lifetime of the returned memcg. Caller is responsible
for the lifetime of the page; \fB__unlock_page_memcg\fP is available
when \fIpage\fP might get freed inside the locked section.
